<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by judee:
[I]A difficult decision. If I were playing a mage I'd go for the vitality and magic, but I assume you're playing a fighter type.

One thing I'd point out - if you hit hard enough you won't need the extra frost and poison, will you? Seems to me a few whacks would get rid of the enemy before the poison really has time to do much, assuming poison in this game acts over time, and not just one "hit". Looks to me like the hard hitter is hard enough to compensate for any other advantages of the second sword.

But that's just how I would play it, and I'm only in the demo, so you may want some advice from a few veteran warriors out there. 

Nice choices to have though!  :)
judee[/I][/QUOTE]

